# Copy this file to `.env.local` and uncomment whichever line you need.
# `.env.local` is gitignored, so your overrides stay on your machine.
#
# Usual case — DO NOTHING. The dev defaults already point at:
#   API helper       → http://localhost:9000   (start with `npm run server:api`)
#   Signaling helper → http://localhost:9001   (start with `npm run server:peerjs`)
#
# Override only if you want non-default behaviour. To customize the helper
# server lists at runtime, edit them under Settings → Helper servers in the
# running app. The legacy single-URL env var is no longer wired in.

# Server-side: override the port either helper listens on.
# (read by parsePort() in server/lib/cli.ts; nothing in the browser bundle uses this)
# PORT=9100
